240
00:13:54,167 --> 00:13:56,100
THEY WON'T DO MY PLAY.

241
00:13:56,169 --> 00:13:58,002
THEY'RE HUMORING ME             
FOR RACHEL'S SAKE.

242
00:13:58,071 --> 00:14:00,371
[SIGHS]             
            THEATER OWNERS.

243
00:14:00,439 --> 00:14:02,907
THOSE LACK-BRAINS KNOW  
        IT'S MY COMEBACK ROLE.

244
00:14:04,978 --> 00:14:09,347
TUCCIO, I'M         
            MORE DEVOTED TO YOU

245
00:14:09,415 --> 00:14:11,582
THAN TO             
            THE ENTIRE WORLD.

246
00:14:13,786 --> 00:14:16,620
"TO THE ENTIRE WORLD."

247
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:18,856
WHO DOESN'T REMEMBER    
        THAT LINE, EH?

248
00:14:18,925 --> 00:14:20,424
ALL THOSE YEARS AGO?

249
00:14:23,997 --> 00:14:27,464
Celimene: OH, LOOK AT       
    HOW MANY UGLY PEOPLE

250
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:28,866
THERE ARE IN THE WORLD.

251
00:14:28,935 --> 00:14:31,035
NO WONDER THEY PAY US       
        SO MUCH MONEY.

252
00:14:32,505 --> 00:14:33,871
CELIMENE IS LOOKING 
            THIS WAY.

253
00:14:35,408 --> 00:14:36,908
SHE'S PUT ON    
                SOME WEIGHT, EH?

254
00:14:36,976 --> 00:14:38,042
AH, YEAH.

255
00:14:39,412 --> 00:14:41,112
OVERRATED TART.

256
00:14:41,180 --> 00:14:43,747
MACARONI QUEEN.

257
00:14:45,151 --> 00:14:47,718
SCORPIONS IN YOUR UNDERWEAR.

258
00:14:47,787 --> 00:14:51,288
THOU WHORESON LITTLE TIDY   
    BARTHOLOMEW BOAR-PIG.

259
00:14:51,357 --> 00:14:53,958
HA HA HA!                       
GOOD TO SEE YOU!

260
00:14:54,027 --> 00:14:56,728
WAIT FOR ME AT THE END  
        OF THE VILLAGE STREET.

261
00:14:56,796 --> 00:14:58,229
I'M GOING TO GET        
        WHAT IS NECESSARY.

262
00:14:58,297 --> 00:15:00,031
I'LL BE BACK.

263
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:02,033
THEN YOU...                     
                    AHH!

264
00:15:02,102 --> 00:15:04,002
AH! THAT MEANS YOU HAVE         
GIVEN ME YOUR WORD.

265
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:05,703
YOU'RE A MAN,                   
NEIGHBOR TURRIDU.

266
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:07,939
WHY IS          
                MY SWORD BENT?

267
00:15:08,008 --> 00:15:10,341
IT GIVES IT A HISTORY.      
    YOU'RE A CARABINIERE.

268
00:15:10,409 --> 00:15:11,709
<i>  LA FIAMMA!</i>

269
00:15:11,778 --> 00:15:13,210
A HEROIC ONE.               
                    RIDICULOUS.

270
00:15:13,279 --> 00:15:14,979
I WAS IN FRANCOFONTE,           
IF YOU MUST KNOW.

271
00:15:15,048 --> 00:15:16,881
PUBLIC HUMILIATION.

272
00:15:16,950 --> 00:15:18,282
IT'S ARTISTIC       
            SUICIDE.

273
00:15:18,351 --> 00:15:20,417
SEND ME ON          
            WITH NO LINES,

274
00:15:20,486 --> 00:15:22,253
GIVE MY PART        
            TO PIERO.

275
00:15:22,321 --> 00:15:25,156
TO PIERO! YOU'RE        
        PLAYING MY PART, CUNT!

276
00:15:36,736 --> 00:15:38,602
[MUSIC BEGINS]

277
00:16:29,689 --> 00:16:32,724
[APPLAUSE]

278
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:42,200
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

279
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:55,779
WAS I GOOD?

280
00:16:55,848 --> 00:16:57,281
BRAVISSIMO.

281
00:16:58,418 --> 00:16:59,817
HOW WAS I?

282
00:16:59,886 --> 00:17:00,951
BRAVISSIMO.

283
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,820
BEAUTIFUL       
                EASTER MORNING.

284
00:17:02,889 --> 00:17:04,088
Man:                    
    LOOK, IT'S RACHEL.

285
00:17:08,161 --> 00:17:11,129
EH, SANTUZZA,                   
GOING TO CONFESSION?

286
00:17:11,197 --> 00:17:14,032
GO BACK IN THE HOUSE AND
        MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

287
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:17,035
ALWAYS PROVOKING.       
        BAD EXCUSE FOR A WIFE.

288
00:17:17,103 --> 00:17:18,869
You can't       
                come this way.

289
00:17:18,938 --> 00:17:20,738
Rachel: MAMA NUNZIA!

290
00:17:20,806 --> 00:17:23,507
AH, IT'S YOU.                   
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

291
00:17:23,576 --> 00:17:26,277
TELL ME WHERE       
            YOUR SON TURRIDU IS.

292
00:17:26,346 --> 00:17:27,711
YOU HAVE THE GALL               
TO ASK ME THAT?

293
00:17:27,780 --> 00:17:30,781
YOU LOOKING FOR TURRIDU HERE? 
  NO! HE'S NOT!

294
00:17:30,850 --> 00:17:32,650
WHEN YOU WRITE...

295
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:34,252
MM-HMM?

296
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:37,355
I PRESS MY FOREHEAD AS HARD 
    AS I CAN AGAINST YOUR DOOR

297
00:17:37,424 --> 00:17:39,323
TO GIVE YOU INSPIRATION.

298
00:17:39,392 --> 00:17:40,858
YOU SHOULD                      
PRESS HARDER.

299
00:17:40,927 --> 00:17:43,694
THERE'S A NAIL STUCK
            RIGHT INTO MY HEART.

300
00:17:43,763 --> 00:17:45,296
TELL IT                         
TO THE DEAD!

301
00:17:45,365 --> 00:17:47,098
[COOING]

302
00:17:47,167 --> 00:17:49,167
[COOING]

303
00:17:49,235 --> 00:17:51,169
I'VE COME TO CELEBRATE  
        EASTER AT HOME,

304
00:17:51,237 --> 00:17:52,437
MAMA NUNZIA.

305
00:17:52,505 --> 00:17:53,837
HAVE YOU ANY        
            OF THE GOOD WINE?

306
00:17:53,906 --> 00:17:56,740
AH, MASTER ALFIO.               
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

307
00:17:58,044 --> 00:17:59,910
I WAS IN FRANCOFONTE,   
        IF YOU MUST KNOW.

308
00:17:59,979 --> 00:18:01,745
TURRIDU WAS                     
SUPPOSED TO BRING

309
00:18:01,814 --> 00:18:03,514
SOME WINE BACK                  
FROM FRANCOFONTE.

310
00:18:03,583 --> 00:18:05,116
YOUR SON TURRIDU    
            IS STILL HERE.

311
00:18:05,185 --> 00:18:07,418
I SAW HIM THIS MORNING  
        AROUND MY PLACE.

312
00:18:07,487 --> 00:18:10,054
HE WAS RUNNING LIKE     
        HE WAS IN A BIG HURRY.

313
00:18:10,123 --> 00:18:15,093
QUITE ONE OF THE FAMILY NOW,
    AREN'T YOU, MISS SANTA?

314
00:18:16,862 --> 00:18:18,562
LOOK THE WAY HE MOVES.

315
00:18:18,631 --> 00:18:21,666
BEAUTIFUL, BEAUTIFUL MAN.

316
00:18:21,734 --> 00:18:23,301
GET OUT! NOW!

317
00:18:23,369 --> 00:18:24,302
NOTE THIS.

318
00:18:24,370 --> 00:18:26,070
SANTUZZA...

319
00:18:26,138 --> 00:18:29,974
YOU MUST THROW YOURSELF AT  
    THE FEET OF THE CRUCIFIED!

320
00:18:34,581 --> 00:18:36,380
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU.

321
00:18:36,449 --> 00:18:37,681
HERE IN THE MIDDLE  
            OF THE STREET?

322
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:39,383
IT DOESN'T MATTER TO ME.

323
00:18:39,452 --> 00:18:40,851
TELL ME WHERE YOU WERE          
LAST NIGHT.

324
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:41,852
HO HO!

325
00:18:41,921 --> 00:18:42,786
HO HO!

326
00:18:45,691 --> 00:18:48,559
WHAT DOES THIS SIGNIFY?

327
00:18:48,628 --> 00:18:50,561
I WAS WHERE IT                  
PLEASED ME TO BE.

328
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:52,029
I WAS IN FRANCOFONTE,         
  IF YOU WANT TO KNOW.

329
00:18:52,098 --> 00:18:54,465
I WAS IN FRANCOFONTE,   
        IF YOU MUST KNOW!

330
00:18:54,534 --> 00:18:56,167
THAT'S RIGHT.

331
00:18:56,236 --> 00:18:57,568
YOU KIDS, SHH!                  
                    QUIET!

332
00:18:57,637 --> 00:18:59,136
YOU STILL LOVE HER.

333
00:18:59,205 --> 00:19:00,171
OH, SHUT--SHUT UP!

334
00:19:00,240 --> 00:19:03,741
I WON'T SHUT UP!            
    I HAVE RABIES IN MY HEART!

335
00:19:03,809 --> 00:19:07,245
YOU'RE CRAZY WITH               
THIS JEALOUSY OF YOURS!

336
00:19:09,415 --> 00:19:11,716
YOU'RE CRAZY WITH               
THIS JEALOUSY OF YOURS!

337
00:19:14,987 --> 00:19:16,720
YOU'RE ACTING LIKE              
I--I WAS A LITTLE BOY

338
00:19:16,789 --> 00:19:18,022
AND I DIDN'T HAVE THE RIGHT     
TO DO WHAT I WANT!

339
00:19:18,090 --> 00:19:19,390
I WANT TO DO WHAT I WANT        
WHEN I WANT TO DO IT!

340
00:19:19,459 --> 00:19:22,727
UNTIL NOW--THANK GOD I HAVE     
NO COLLAR AROUND MY NECK!

341
00:19:22,795 --> 00:19:23,961
WHAT WILL I DO      
            IF YOU ABANDON ME?

342
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:25,095
I'M NOT!

343
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:27,698
WHAT'S HE DOING? HE'S       
    CHANGING ALL THE BLOCKING.

344
00:19:27,767 --> 00:19:31,135
I'M NOT ABANDONING YOU.

345
00:19:31,204 --> 00:19:32,537
THIS IS GOOD.

346
00:19:32,605 --> 00:19:34,205
THIS IS SPONTANEOUS.        
    I LIKE THIS.

347
00:19:34,274 --> 00:19:35,439
NO!

348
00:19:35,508 --> 00:19:36,907
I AM NOT ABANDONING YOU!

349
00:19:36,976 --> 00:19:38,242
KILL ME! KILL ME!

350
00:19:38,311 --> 00:19:39,243
"Blood of Judas!"

351
00:19:39,312 --> 00:19:40,744
I DON'T CARE ANYMORE!           
KILL ME!

352
00:19:40,813 --> 00:19:42,046
DO IT.                  
                        "Judas."

353
00:19:42,114 --> 00:19:44,148
I CAN'T MOVE BACKWARDS          
OR FORWARDS!

354
00:19:44,217 --> 00:19:46,651
I'M TIED TO                   
  YOUR APRON STRINGS.

355
00:19:46,719 --> 00:19:48,653
I DON'T KNOW WHERE              
I AM ANYMORE.

356
00:19:48,721 --> 00:19:51,121
PLEASE, DON'T LEAVE ME!

357
00:19:51,191 --> 00:19:53,224
TURRIDU, DON'T LEAVE ME!

358
00:19:53,293 --> 00:19:54,224
TURRIDU!

359
00:19:54,293 --> 00:19:56,227
"Blood of Judas."

360
00:19:56,296 --> 00:19:58,663
TURRIDU, DON'T LEAVE ME!

361
00:19:58,731 --> 00:20:01,098
OHH...

362
00:20:01,166 --> 00:20:03,934
[PANTING] MOTHER?

363
00:20:05,238 --> 00:20:06,270
MOTHER!

364
00:20:06,339 --> 00:20:09,273
MOTHER, EMBRACE ME NOW          
AS YOU DID WHEN I LEFT

365
00:20:09,342 --> 00:20:12,643
TO BECOME A SOLDIER,            
BECAUSE TODAY IS EASTER.

366
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:15,413
TURRIDU.            
            DON'T LEAVE ME.

367
00:20:15,481 --> 00:20:18,749
WONDERFUL. I'VE NEVER, EVER 
    SEEN ANYTHING SO REAL.

368
00:20:20,119 --> 00:20:22,186
TURRIDU...

369
00:20:22,255 --> 00:20:23,454
DON'T LEAVE ME.

370
00:20:23,523 --> 00:20:25,856
TURRIDU...

371
00:20:25,925 --> 00:20:27,425
GO ON WITH THE PLAY.

372
00:20:28,561 --> 00:20:29,627
TURRIDU!

373
00:20:29,696 --> 00:20:32,796
THIS IS WHAT HAPPENS            
WHEN AN ACTOR IS MISCAST.

374
00:20:32,865 --> 00:20:33,864
TURRIDU!

375
00:20:33,933 --> 00:20:35,766
IS HE DEAD?

376
00:20:35,835 --> 00:20:36,900
TURRIDU!

377
00:20:44,810 --> 00:20:46,444
I THINK             
            THERE'S A PROBLEM.

378
00:20:46,512 --> 00:20:47,845
I DIDN'T SEE
                    ANY BLOOD.

379
00:20:47,913 --> 00:20:49,747
THERE ISN'T ANY BLOOD.          
IT'S A SYMBOL.

380
00:20:49,815 --> 00:20:51,749
EITHER YOUR INTELLIGENCE        
IS SUFFICIENT

381
00:20:51,817 --> 00:20:54,118
TO UNDERSTAND SYMBOLS           
OR IT ISN'T.

382
00:20:54,186 --> 00:20:55,686
YOURS IS INSUFFICIENT.

383
00:20:55,755 --> 00:20:57,321
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,       
        THERE WILL BE

384
00:20:57,390 --> 00:21:01,692
A BRIEF BUT SEATED...       
        INTERMISSION.

385
00:21:01,761 --> 00:21:05,463
THERE IS NOTHING I LIKE BETTER  
THAN THINGS LIKE THIS.

386
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:08,966
WELL?

387
00:21:09,034 --> 00:21:09,967
HE'S ALIVE.

388
00:21:10,035 --> 00:21:11,101
CAN HE ACT?

389
00:21:11,170 --> 00:21:13,036
I'LL PLAY   
                    TURRIDU!

390
00:21:13,105 --> 00:21:14,538
YOU ARE NOT PLAYING 
            THAT PART.

391
00:21:14,607 --> 00:21:15,873
IT'S ALWAYS                 
    BEEN MY PART!

392
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:17,475
I AM THE MANAGER    
            OF THIS COMPANY.

393
00:21:17,543 --> 00:21:19,076
WHAT HAVE I DONE            
    TO MAKE YOU

394
00:21:19,145 --> 00:21:20,177
CONTINUALLY PUNISH ME       
    THIS WAY?

395
00:21:20,246 --> 00:21:21,679
"HO HO!"    
APART FROM THAT.

396
00:21:21,748 --> 00:21:24,148
YOUR PERFORMANCE LAST NIGHT 
    WAS A TOOTH-PULLER.

397
00:21:24,216 --> 00:21:25,616
YOU FUCKED ALL DAY!

398
00:21:25,685 --> 00:21:27,117
THIS BUSINESS IS        
        BASED ON FORNICATION.

399
00:21:27,186 --> 00:21:30,454
"TOOTH-PULLER"?                 
THIS TIME YOU GO TOO FAR.

400
00:21:30,523 --> 00:21:32,055
Flavio: SILENCE!

401
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:35,593
LET US START            
        A GENERAL TOPIC!

402
00:21:35,662 --> 00:21:39,730
LET IT BE...            
    "THE ORIGINS OF DRAMA."

403
00:21:42,502 --> 00:21:44,702
I WILL SPEAK SECOND.

404
00:21:44,771 --> 00:21:47,037
[BOOING AND WHISTLING]

405
00:21:48,675 --> 00:21:51,909
SHH!    
SHH!

406
00:21:53,045 --> 00:21:55,846
I CAN SMELL POWDER.         
        I LIKE THAT.

407
00:21:55,915 --> 00:21:57,581
[LAUGHTER]

408
00:22:03,455 --> 00:22:06,023
I KNEW A MAN ONCE...

409
00:22:06,092 --> 00:22:08,525
WHO ASKED HIS WIFE...

410
00:22:08,594 --> 00:22:11,328
"HOW DO YOU WANT ME         
    TO LOVE YOU?"

411
00:22:11,396 --> 00:22:15,099
THE MAN BECAME INFATUATED   
    WITH ANOTHER WOMAN.

412
00:22:15,167 --> 00:22:19,136
"DO YOU WANT ME TO LOVE YOU 
    WITHOUT SUFFERING?"

413
00:22:19,205 --> 00:22:21,872
HE FORCED HIS WIFE          
    INTO THE HUMILIATION

414
00:22:21,941 --> 00:22:24,875
OF INVITING THE OTHER WOMAN 
        TO DINNER.

415
00:22:24,944 --> 00:22:28,212
"DO YOU WANT ME TO LOVE YOU 
        WITHOUT CRUELTY?"

416
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:32,216
HE SPENT THE ENTIRE EVENING 
    SITTING NEXT TO THIS WOMAN

417
00:22:32,284 --> 00:22:35,619
WHILE HIS WIFE          
    SAT ALONE AND SILENT

418
00:22:35,687 --> 00:22:38,055
LOOKING OUT A WINDOW        
    INTO THE NIGHT.

419
00:22:38,124 --> 00:22:41,058
THE OTHER WOMAN             
    RAN OUT OF THE HOUSE.

420
00:22:41,127 --> 00:22:42,993
HE RAN AFTER HER,           
    IN THE RAIN,

421
00:22:43,062 --> 00:22:46,563
RUNNING THROUGH THE STREETS,
    SCREAMING HER NAME.

422
00:22:46,632 --> 00:22:49,466
HE DIDN'T FIND HER.

423
00:22:49,534 --> 00:22:52,870
HE CAME HOME.

424
00:22:52,938 --> 00:22:56,240
HIS WIFE HAD DRUNK IODINE.

425
00:22:58,410 --> 00:23:01,111
"HOW COULD YOU?"        
        HE SHOOK HER.

426
00:23:03,682 --> 00:23:05,082
"HOW COULD YOU?"

427
00:23:07,286 --> 00:23:11,955
"I CANNOT THINK OF LIFE     
        WITHOUT YOU."

428
00:23:12,024 --> 00:23:15,425
SHE...VOMITED.

429
00:23:16,595 --> 00:23:19,129
"DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND

430
00:23:19,198 --> 00:23:22,532
"WHAT A BEAUTIFUL LOVE      
    I WOULD LIKE TO GIVE YOU

431
00:23:22,601 --> 00:23:23,600
IN LOVING YOU?"

432
00:23:26,371 --> 00:23:29,539
SHE WENT ON VOMITING.

433
00:23:29,608 --> 00:23:32,309
"WHAT A BEAUTIFUL LOVE

434
00:23:32,377 --> 00:23:34,278
I WOULD LIKE TO GIVE YOU."

435
00:23:38,017 --> 00:23:44,321
WHAT A DELUSION TO BELIEVE  
    THERE IS ORDER OR LOGIC

436
00:23:44,389 --> 00:23:46,190
IN THE EVENTS OF OUR LIVES.

437
00:23:46,258 --> 00:23:49,392
THIS AFTERNOON          
    YOU CAME TO SEE A PLAY,

438
00:23:49,461 --> 00:23:52,762
A PLAY WITH THE ACTOR PIERO 
        PLAYING A ROLE

439
00:23:52,832 --> 00:23:55,532
IN WHICH HE WAS TO HAVE     
    DIED A JEALOUS DEATH,

440
00:23:55,600 --> 00:24:00,370
AN IMAGINED...JEALOUS DEATH.

441
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:05,142
AND NOW...              
    THE UNIMAGINABLE HAS STRUCK.

442
00:24:05,211 --> 00:24:08,812
PIERO...

443
00:24:08,881 --> 00:24:11,381
OUR PIERO...

444
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:14,852
<i>  THE</i>  PIERO...

445
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:16,220
IS GONE.

446
00:24:18,057 --> 00:24:20,590
YES...

447
00:24:20,659 --> 00:24:22,993
HE DIES FOR REAL.

448
00:24:26,565 --> 00:24:28,665
A MOMENT, PLEASE.

449
00:24:34,373 --> 00:24:38,408
HE DIED?            
    HE HAD SUCH POTENTIAL.

450
00:24:38,477 --> 00:24:39,843
DID HE SAY I'M DEAD?
            I'M NOT DEAD.

451
00:24:39,912 --> 00:24:41,778
SHH. YOU'LL COME BACK.

452
00:24:41,847 --> 00:24:44,247
Tuccio:             
    THERE IS ANOTHER PLAY

453
00:24:44,316 --> 00:24:47,650
SPAWNED IN THE STORY        
    I HAVE JUST TOLD YOU.

454
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:50,620
A PLAY OF MINE...

455
00:24:50,689 --> 00:24:54,324
TO BE PERFORMED TOMORROW.

456
00:24:54,393 --> 00:24:55,558
<i>  ILLUMINATA.</i>

457
00:24:55,627 --> 00:24:57,460
Man: LET'S SEE IT TONIGHT!

458
00:24:57,529 --> 00:24:59,263
I PAID FOR A PLAY!              
I WANT TO SEE A PLAY!

459
00:25:05,237 --> 00:25:08,205
YOU FLATTER ME          
    WITH YOUR ENTHUSIASM,

460
00:25:08,274 --> 00:25:09,873
BUT IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.        
        THE ACTORS--

461
00:25:09,942 --> 00:25:11,909
I AM READY!

462
00:25:13,879 --> 00:25:17,580
IF YOU MUST SEE IT,         
    THEN YOU LEAVE US NO CHOICE.

463
00:25:21,053 --> 00:25:24,054
THIS TUCCIO...

464
00:25:24,123 --> 00:25:26,390
FIND OUT            
            HOW HE TASTES.

465
00:25:26,458 --> 00:25:27,557
COULDN'T WAIT.

466
00:25:27,626 --> 00:25:29,026
I'M FINISHED
                    WAITING.

467
00:25:29,094 --> 00:25:30,693
THE OPPORTUNITY WAS 
            THERE AND I TOOK IT.

468
00:25:30,762 --> 00:25:33,530
YES, YOU TOOK IT.           
    AND WITHOUT A WORD TO ME.

469
00:25:33,598 --> 00:25:35,532
I HAVE TO PERFORM IT.       
    DID YOU CONSIDER THAT?

470
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:38,701
I WOULDN'T HAVE GONE OUT THERE  
IF I DIDN'T FEEL IN MY HEART...

471
00:25:38,770 --> 00:25:41,171
AND WITH ALL MY BEING...

