00:48:23,133 --> 00:48:26,669
EVERYONE IS SEEING IT.          
HE'S THE RAGE.

948
00:48:30,908 --> 00:48:32,308
YOU'D DO THIS<i>  DOLL'S HOUSE?</i>

949
00:48:32,376 --> 00:48:33,809
Rachel: NOW'S           
        NOT THE TIME, TUCCIO.

950
00:48:33,877 --> 00:48:34,943
FOR ME, IT IS.

951
00:48:35,012 --> 00:48:37,263
MY TIME--IT'S NOT YOUR PLAY.    
IT'S MY PLAY.

952
00:48:37,332 --> 00:48:38,314
OH, GOD,            
            THIS SELFISHNESS--

953
00:48:38,382 --> 00:48:40,716
"MY PLAY. MY PLAY." 
            I CAN'T STAND IT.

954
00:48:40,784 --> 00:48:42,501
MAYBE THIS IBSEN                
IS MORE TO YOUR LIKING.

955
00:48:42,570 --> 00:48:43,535
YES.        
                    MAYBE HE IS.

956
00:48:43,604 --> 00:48:45,588
GOOD.               MAYBE       
THEN DO HIM.        I WILL.

957
00:48:45,656 --> 00:48:47,323
DON'T SAY MAYBE.

958
00:48:47,391 --> 00:48:49,525
GO AHEAD.               
        DO HIM.

959
00:48:49,594 --> 00:48:51,560
GO TO PALLENCHIO      
          RIGHT NOW.

960
00:48:51,629 --> 00:48:54,230
TELL HIM,               
        "I, THE GREAT RACHEL,

961
00:48:54,298 --> 00:48:56,265
"LOVER TO               
        THE MEDIOCRITY TUCCIO,

962
00:48:56,334 --> 00:48:58,434
"AM HERE TO EAT.

963
00:48:58,502 --> 00:49:00,536
"GIVE ME IBSEN          
        AND SOME SAUSAGE.

964
00:49:00,605 --> 00:49:01,520
I AM READY."

965
00:49:01,589 --> 00:49:03,572
I AM SURE, AS ALWAYS,

966
00:49:03,641 --> 00:49:05,173
YOU'LL TRANSFORM        
        THE MOMENT

967
00:49:05,243 --> 00:49:07,008
INTO SOMETHING...

968
00:49:07,077 --> 00:49:08,310
INCANDESCENT.

969
00:49:16,887 --> 00:49:17,819
Dominique:                      
TUCCIO--

970
00:49:17,888 --> 00:49:18,820
IT'S HER LIFE.

971
00:49:18,889 --> 00:49:20,155
LET HER LIVE IT 
                AS SHE SEES FIT.

972
00:49:20,224 --> 00:49:21,590
TUCCIO, TO DO                   
THIS IBSEN PLAY

973
00:49:21,659 --> 00:49:23,325
DOESN'T MEAN                    
SHE'S FINISHED WITH YOU.

974
00:49:23,394 --> 00:49:25,327
ARE YOU SPEAKING
                FOR RACHEL

975
00:49:25,396 --> 00:49:26,828
OR FOR YOURSELF,
                DOMINIQUE?

976
00:49:26,897 --> 00:49:28,029
HOW AM I TO TAKE THAT?

977
00:49:28,098 --> 00:49:30,098
WELL, TAKE IT       
            ANY WAY YOU CHOOSE.

978
00:49:30,167 --> 00:49:31,333
AND WHAT IF I CHOOSE            
TO RESENT IT?

979
00:49:31,402 --> 00:49:32,901
WE'VE BEEN FRIENDS          
    A LONG TIME, TUCCIO.

980
00:49:32,970 --> 00:49:34,236
FRIENDSHIP              
        MUST BE TESTED

981
00:49:34,305 --> 00:49:35,337
EVERY ONCE IN A WHILE.

982
00:49:35,406 --> 00:49:36,405
YOU SHOULD GO BACK TO HER,

983
00:49:36,474 --> 00:49:37,506
IF YOU DON'T MIND           
    MY SAYING SO.

984
00:49:37,575 --> 00:49:38,540
I, TO HER?

985
00:49:38,609 --> 00:49:39,808
DO YOU EXPECT ME                
TO REFUSE THIS IBSEN PLAY?

986
00:49:39,877 --> 00:49:41,243
I EXPECT NOTHING.

987
00:49:43,180 --> 00:49:45,113
OUR LIVES           
            WIND THEMSELVES OUT.

988
00:49:47,017 --> 00:49:50,519
WHEN THEY WIND TOGETHER,
        THAT IS SOMETHING FINE

989
00:49:50,588 --> 00:49:51,453
AND RARE.

990
00:49:52,757 --> 00:49:54,290
WHEN THEY UNRAVEL,      
        I'LL LEAVE IT TO OTHERS

991
00:49:54,358 --> 00:49:55,857
TO DIAGNOSE THE CAUSE.

992
00:50:01,916 --> 00:50:03,699
I'LL SEND A LETTER          
    TO THE MAGISTRATE

993
00:50:03,768 --> 00:50:05,033
ON YOUR FATHER'S BEHALF.

994
00:50:05,102 --> 00:50:06,635
WE'LL DO ALL WE CAN,

995
00:50:06,704 --> 00:50:08,170
BUT I BEG YOU, RACHEL,

996
00:50:08,238 --> 00:50:09,672
DON'T MIX               
    YOUR LOVE AND YOUR ART.

997
00:50:09,740 --> 00:50:12,675
YOU DO VIOLENCE             
    TO YOUR NATURE, YOUR TALENT.

998
00:50:12,743 --> 00:50:14,610
I NEED SOMETHING NEW.

999
00:50:14,679 --> 00:50:15,911
TUCCIO'S PLAY--

1000
00:50:15,979 --> 00:50:17,379
TUCCIO'S PLAY?

1001
00:50:17,448 --> 00:50:18,681
BELONGS TO MY TIME.

1002
00:50:18,749 --> 00:50:20,215
HAS NO ENDING.

1003
00:50:20,284 --> 00:50:21,967
IT IS IN THE AIR
                THAT I BREATHE.

1004
00:50:22,036 --> 00:50:23,285
DO<i>  CAMILLE.</i>

1005
00:50:23,354 --> 00:50:25,120
THE PEOPLE                    
  LOVE YOU IN<i>  CAMILLE.</i>

1006
00:50:25,189 --> 00:50:26,322
JUST BECAUSE            
        YOU LOVE HIM

1007
00:50:26,390 --> 00:50:28,457
DOESN'T MAKE HIM            
    A GREAT DRAMATIST.

1008
00:50:28,526 --> 00:50:29,625
DO YOU THINK            
    YOU'RE THE ONLY WOMAN

1009
00:50:29,694 --> 00:50:31,193
THAT'S EVER             
    BEEN FOOLED BY A MAN?

1010
00:50:31,261 --> 00:50:33,328
CELIMENE DRAGGED HER LOVER  
        AROUND FOR YEARS

1011
00:50:33,397 --> 00:50:35,397
FOISTING HIM            
        UPON AUDIENCES.

1012
00:50:35,466 --> 00:50:36,898
HE WAS BEAUTIFUL.

1013
00:50:36,967 --> 00:50:37,899
HE WAS A DONKEY.

1014
00:50:37,968 --> 00:50:40,035
YOU COMPARE TUCCIO  
            TO CELIMENE'S WHORE?

1015
00:50:40,103 --> 00:50:41,670
OH, HE WAS A WHORE.             
SHE'S RIGHT.

1016
00:50:41,739 --> 00:50:43,238
BUT WHAT A WHORE.

1017
00:50:43,307 --> 00:50:45,741
QUIET.              
        THE POINT IS...

1018
00:50:45,810 --> 00:50:47,810
THAT THE TEST           
        OF AN ARTIST

1019
00:50:47,878 --> 00:50:50,779
IS IF HE CAN STAND          
        ON HIS OWN.

1020
00:50:50,848 --> 00:50:53,515
WOULD TUCCIO            
    BE DONE WITHOUT YOU?

1021
00:50:53,584 --> 00:50:55,651
NO, NEVER.                      
LISTEN...

1022
00:50:55,720 --> 00:50:57,919
IN TUCCIO'S PLAY,               
THE HUSBAND BETRAYS THE WIFE,

1023
00:50:57,988 --> 00:50:59,054
AND WHAT DOES SHE DO?

1024
00:50:59,122 --> 00:51:00,889
SHE DOESN'T TAKE REVENGE.       
SHE DOESN'T KILL HIM.

1025
00:51:00,958 --> 00:51:01,974
SHE DOESN'T EVEN LEAVE HIM.

1026
00:51:02,042 --> 00:51:04,326
SHE GOES ON LOVING HIM.

1027
00:51:04,394 --> 00:51:06,829
THAT'S HIS ENDING.

1028
00:51:06,897 --> 00:51:08,797
IT'S RIDICULOUS.

1029
00:51:08,866 --> 00:51:11,099
DID YOU EVER SEE              
  THE END OF<i>  ANTONY?</i>

1030
00:51:11,168 --> 00:51:12,368
DO YOU KNOW                   
  HOW<i>  ANTONY</i>  ENDS?

1031
00:51:12,436 --> 00:51:14,603
THE ENDING OF<i>  ANTONY?</i>

1032
00:51:14,672 --> 00:51:17,439
ANTONY'S MISTRESS HEARS         
HER HUSBAND'S FOOTSTEPS.

1033
00:51:17,508 --> 00:51:19,842
THE HUSBAND HAS RETURNED        
UNEXPECTEDLY,

1034
00:51:19,910 --> 00:51:21,042
SO, ANTONY,                     
OF COURSE, SUGGESTS

1035
00:51:21,111 --> 00:51:23,579
THAT HE AND THE LADY            
SHOULD CLEAR OUT.

1036
00:51:23,647 --> 00:51:24,946
"OH, NO," SHE SAYS,

1037
00:51:25,015 --> 00:51:27,015
"I MUST KEEP                    
MY REPUTATION."

1038
00:51:27,084 --> 00:51:29,435
SO, WITH THE HUSBAND            
COMING UP THE STAIRS,

1039
00:51:29,504 --> 00:51:31,987
ANTONY STABS HER                
THROUGH THE HEART,

1040
00:51:32,055 --> 00:51:33,622
FLINGS OPEN THE DOOR,           
AND SAYS,

1041
00:51:33,691 --> 00:51:37,058
"I KILLED HER                   
WITH THIS DAGGER.

1042
00:51:37,127 --> 00:51:38,927
SHE RESISTED ME."

1043
00:51:40,998 --> 00:51:42,798
WHAT A CURIOUS WAY  
            TO PRESERVE

1044
00:51:42,867 --> 00:51:44,266
A LADY'S REPUTATION.

1045
00:51:44,334 --> 00:51:46,402
YOU THINK SO? WELL,             
THE AUDIENCE WENT WILD--

1046
00:51:46,470 --> 00:51:47,770
ESPECIALLY                      
IN THE CHEAPER SEATS.

1047
00:51:47,838 --> 00:51:50,439
BUT NOT JUST HERE               
IN AMERICA--ALL OVER.

1048
00:51:50,508 --> 00:51:53,275
ALL THE GREAT ENDINGS.

1049
00:51:53,343 --> 00:51:55,444
OEDIPUS HAS SEX                 
WITH HIS MOTHER,

1050
00:51:55,513 --> 00:51:56,945
AND, WHAT?                      
HE SAYS, "I'M SORRY"?

1051
00:51:57,014 --> 00:51:59,047
HE TEARS HIS EYES OUT.

1052
00:51:59,116 --> 00:52:01,316
OTHELLO THINKS                  
HIS WIFE AND CASSIO--

1053
00:52:01,385 --> 00:52:02,317
HE THINKS,

1054
00:52:02,386 --> 00:52:05,754
AND HE KILLS HER                
AND HIMSELF.

1055
00:52:05,823 --> 00:52:06,855
<i>  HAMLET--</i>

1056
00:52:06,924 --> 00:52:08,824
EVERYBODY DIES.

1057
00:52:08,893 --> 00:52:11,794
<i>  PHAEDRA.</i>                      
  THESE ARE PLAYS.

1058
00:52:11,862 --> 00:52:13,495
SO WHY DON'T YOU DO 
            THESE PLAYS?

1059
00:52:13,564 --> 00:52:15,597
WHY? BECAUSE NOBODY WANTS       
TO SEE THEM, THAT'S WHY.

1060
00:52:15,666 --> 00:52:19,267
BUT THAT DOESN'T TAKE AWAY      
FROM THEIR ENDINGS.

1061
00:52:19,336 --> 00:52:22,370
WHENEVER I HAVE TO DO   
        A DEATH SCENE,

1062
00:52:22,440 --> 00:52:25,607
I THINK ONE DAY         
        I WILL REALLY DIE...

1063
00:52:27,044 --> 00:52:29,077
AND ON THAT DAY,        
        I'LL REMEMBER

1064
00:52:29,146 --> 00:52:31,379
I ONCE ACTED A PARODY

1065
00:52:31,449 --> 00:52:32,781
OF MY OWN DYING MOMENTS.

1066
00:52:34,785 --> 00:52:36,318
WHEN THE SOUL   
                REMEMBERS...

1067
00:52:37,922 --> 00:52:39,287
WHAT WILL IT SAY?

1068
00:52:46,363 --> 00:52:47,596
"I GO IN THE WIND..."

1069
00:52:48,966 --> 00:52:52,501
"LIKE SOMEONE           
    WHO KNOWS HIS WAY...

1070
00:52:52,570 --> 00:52:54,503
"THOUGH IN MY HEART,        
    I AM ONLY OBEYING

1071
00:52:54,572 --> 00:52:58,073
"A VOICE THAT           
    CARRIES ME FORWARD--

1072
00:52:58,141 --> 00:52:59,675
ALWAYS FORWARD."

1073
00:53:03,447 --> 00:53:07,816
"WHAT WILL I FIND       
    AT THE END OF SUCH A LIFE?"

1074
00:53:09,152 --> 00:53:10,018
"PERHAPS..."

1075
00:53:11,956 --> 00:53:14,823
"THE SECRET SWEETNESS       
    OF HAVING OBEYED MY FATE?"

1076
00:53:18,762 --> 00:53:19,995
"PERHAPS."

1077
00:53:27,872 --> 00:53:29,805
THAT IS TUCCIO'S WRITING.

1078
00:53:31,575 --> 00:53:33,675
IT SPEAKS TO ME.

1079
00:53:33,744 --> 00:53:36,211
I WILL DO         
        <i>  A DOLL'S HOUSE,</i>

1080
00:53:36,279 --> 00:53:38,514
BUT ONLY IF TUCCIO'S PLAY

1081
00:53:38,582 --> 00:53:40,081
IS GIVEN ANOTHER CHANCE.

1082
00:54:01,104 --> 00:54:02,971
[SNIFFS]

1083
00:54:09,914 --> 00:54:11,780
[READS ALOUD]

1084
00:54:16,620 --> 00:54:18,486
[SIGHS]

1085
00:54:35,138 --> 00:54:37,706
WHERE IS MY CHILD?          
        MY CHILD.

1086
00:54:37,775 --> 00:54:38,707
WHERE IS THE CHILD?

1087
00:54:38,776 --> 00:54:41,476
THE CHILD.              
    WHERE IS THE CHILD?

1088
00:54:41,545 --> 00:54:43,311
WHERE IS THE CHILD?       
      WHERE IS THE CHILD?

1089
00:54:43,364 --> 00:54:44,947
WHERE IS THE CHILD?

1090
00:54:45,015 --> 00:54:45,981
THE CHILD.

1091
00:54:46,050 --> 00:54:47,983
OH, THE CHILD.          
    WHAT HAVE THEY DONE TO YOU?

1092
00:54:48,052 --> 00:54:50,752
OH, MY CHILD,         
      WHAT HAVE THEY DONE TO YO?

1093
00:54:50,821 --> 00:54:52,721
OH, WHAT HAVE THEY DONE?

1094
00:54:52,790 --> 00:54:55,290
[SINGS]

1095
00:54:55,358 --> 00:54:56,792
YOU SLUT.                       
                    WHAT?

1096
00:54:56,860 --> 00:54:57,926
SO THAT'S HOW YOU GET           
YOUR GOOD REVIEWS.

1097
00:54:57,995 --> 00:54:58,927
WHAT?

1098
00:54:58,996 --> 00:55:00,862
LOOK. LOOK AT THIS.             
LOOK.

1099
00:55:02,532 --> 00:55:04,232
HEH HEH HEH!

1100
00:55:04,301 --> 00:55:06,501
OH, UH, UH,                     
UH, UH, UH.

1101
00:55:06,570 --> 00:55:08,670
OH, MY GOD.

1102
00:55:08,739 --> 00:55:09,738
I--I--

1103
00:55:11,508 --> 00:55:12,941
YOU GO.

1104
00:55:13,010 --> 00:55:15,010
YOU HAVE NO CHOICE  
            BUT TO GO.

1105
00:55:15,079 --> 00:55:16,011
BUT HE'LL PORK ME.

1106
00:55:16,080 --> 00:55:18,080
THEN LET HIM AND        
        ACT LIKE YOU LIKE IT.

1107
00:55:18,148 --> 00:55:19,081
NO.                         
            YES!

1108
00:55:19,149 --> 00:55:20,082
I AM NOT. NO!

1109
00:55:20,150 --> 00:55:21,617
YOU GO FOR US!  
    NO. NO.

1110
00:55:21,685 --> 00:55:23,485
FOR THE COMPANY!                
FOR TUCCIO!

1111
00:55:23,553 --> 00:55:24,920
YOU'RE GOING TO GO!

1112
00:55:24,989 --> 00:55:26,688
I AM NOT        YOU ARE GOING   
GOING TO GO!    TO GO!

1113
00:55:26,757 --> 00:55:27,956
YES!        
NO, I'M NOT!

1114
00:55:28,025 --> 00:55:29,625
YES, YOU ARE!

1115
00:55:29,693 --> 00:55:30,558
OW!

1116
00:55:31,729 --> 00:55:32,694
I--

1117
00:55:32,763 --> 00:55:33,695
WHY DON'T YOU GO?

1118
00:55:33,764 --> 00:55:35,664
I WOULD, BUT                    
HE DOESN'T WANT ME.

1119
00:55:35,733 --> 00:55:38,100
I COME ACROSS                   
AS TOO MASCULINE.

1120
00:55:42,539 --> 00:55:45,573
THINK OF MY MOTHER. 
            WHAT WOULD SHE SAY?

1121
00:55:45,643 --> 00:55:48,209
KEEP YOUR MOTHER                
OUT OF THIS FOR ONCE.

1122
00:55:48,278 --> 00:55:49,878
JUST GIVE HIM HOPE.

1123
00:55:49,947 --> 00:55:51,146
LOOK...

1124
00:55:51,214 --> 00:55:54,149
TELL HIM YOU TOOK               
A VOW OF CHASTITY--

1125
00:55:54,217 --> 00:55:55,316
ANYTHING--

1126
00:55:55,385 --> 00:55:56,551
BUT LEAD HIM ON.

1127
00:55:56,620 --> 00:55:58,654
LEAD HIM ON.

1128
00:55:58,722 --> 00:56:01,056
LEAD HIM ON.

1129
00:56:01,125 --> 00:56:02,724
YOU CAN DO IT.

1130
00:56:02,793 --> 00:56:05,027
IT'S EASY.                      
JUST LET YOURSELF GO.

1131
00:56:05,095 --> 00:56:07,295
EASY, EASY.         
            YEAH, EASY FOR YOU.

1132
00:56:07,364 --> 00:56:09,264
YOU'RE GOING TO GO!           
  YOU'RE GOING, I TELL YOU!

1133
00:56:09,332 --> 00:56:10,999
YOU'RE GOING    I'M NOT GOING   
TO DO IT!       TO DO IT!

1134
00:56:11,068 --> 00:56:14,036
ENOUGH!             
        ENOUGH, I SAY!

1135
00:56:14,104 --> 00:56:15,503
YOU ARE ACCUSED

1136
00:56:15,572 --> 00:56:17,472
OF VIOLATING            
    YOUR OATH OF CELIBACY.

1137
00:56:17,541 --> 00:56:18,974
I AM A VIRGIN.

1138
00:56:19,043 --> 00:56:20,142
NONE OF         
                YOUR INSOLENCE.

1139
00:56:20,210 --> 00:56:21,076
STATE YOUR AGE.

1140
00:56:24,514 --> 00:56:25,947
19.

1141
00:56:26,016 --> 00:56:27,883
[APPLAUSE]

1142
00:56:31,155 --> 00:56:33,021
[NUNS SCREAMING]

1143
00:56:43,533 --> 00:56:45,600
UHH...

1144
00:56:56,781 --> 00:56:57,712
I'M HERE--

1145
00:56:57,782 --> 00:56:58,713
WE KNOW.

1146
00:56:58,783 --> 00:57:01,583
WE'VE BEEN WAITING FOR YOU.

1147
00:57:01,652 --> 00:57:03,952
WELCOME TO OUR WORLD.

1148
00:57:04,021 --> 00:57:06,288
[APPLAUSE]

1149
00:57:06,356 --> 00:57:07,722
Man: BRAVA! BRAVA!

1150
00:57:09,160 --> 00:57:10,725
Man: BRAVA!

1151
00:57:10,795 --> 00:57:13,228
Man:                    
    BRAVA! BRAVA! BRAVA!

1152
00:57:16,533 --> 00:57:18,300
BRAVA! BRAVA! BRAVA!

1153
00:57:18,368 --> 00:57:21,069
ALWAYS WEAR     
                FINE UNDERWEAR.

1154
00:57:21,138 --> 00:57:22,337
LEARN THAT.

1155
00:57:22,406 --> 00:57:24,273
I LEARNED IT    
                TOO LATE.

1156
00:57:26,710 --> 00:57:27,575
ENTER.

1157
00:57:29,013 --> 00:57:30,879
[BIRD CHIRPING]

1158
00:57:32,082 --> 00:57:33,515
COME IN, COME IN.

1159
00:57:33,583 --> 00:57:35,250
DON'T BE SHY.

1160
00:57:35,319 --> 00:57:38,453
FEEL FREE TO LOOK   
            THROUGH HER THINGS.

1161
00:57:38,522 --> 00:57:40,488
I DO.

1162
00:57:40,557 --> 00:57:42,757
Celimene: THE PLAY IS CALLED  
    <i>  THE VIRGIN OF AVILA,</i>

1163
00:57:42,827 --> 00:57:44,993
NOT<i>  THE CHILD</i>        
    <i>  OF THE VIRGIN OF AVILA.</i>

1164
00:57:45,062 --> 00:57:45,994
I HAVE TO GO.

1165
00:57:46,063 --> 00:57:46,995
SHE DOESN'T         
            WANT ME NEAR YOU.

1166
00:57:47,064 --> 00:57:48,697
I WANT MY MOON.

1167
00:57:48,765 --> 00:57:50,332
THE STAGE DIRECTIONS READ,

1168
00:57:50,400 --> 00:57:52,234
"THE VIRGIN ADVANCES,

1169
00:57:52,303 --> 00:57:53,535
"PALE IN THE MOONLIGHT,

1170
00:57:53,603 --> 00:57:56,004
CONVULSED WITH EMOTION."

1171
00:57:56,073 --> 00:57:57,472
I AM PALE.

1172
00:57:57,541 --> 00:57:59,174
I AM CONVULSED.

1173
00:57:59,243 --> 00:58:01,276
I WANT MY MOON!

1174
00:58:01,345 --> 00:58:02,811
Man: YES, MA'AM.

1175
00:58:02,880 --> 00:58:04,746
[SIGHS]

1176
00:58:04,815 --> 00:58:06,882
[SIGHS]

1177
00:58:06,951 --> 00:58:10,085
I HAVEN'T ACTED             
    SO WELL IN YEARS.

1178
00:58:10,154 --> 00:58:11,619
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?    
        GET OUT. GET OUT.

1179
00:58:11,688 --> 00:58:14,422
I DON'T WANT TO SEE         
