01:12:02,185 --> 01:12:07,221
♪♪ WHEN WE ARE APART ♪♪

1434
01:12:07,290 --> 01:12:10,024
♪♪ AND THE DAYS ♪♪

1435
01:12:10,093 --> 01:12:13,594
♪♪ SEEM LONELY ♪♪

1436
01:12:16,332 --> 01:12:17,465
MMM.

1437
01:12:17,534 --> 01:12:19,867
OH, MOMMY, MOMMY, MOMMY,    
    MOMMY, MOMMY, MOMMY, MOMMY.

1438
01:12:19,936 --> 01:12:21,536
CAN I CALL YOU MOMMY?

1439
01:12:21,604 --> 01:12:23,604
YOUR NEXT PLAY--        
        YES, I KNOW ABOUT IT,

1440
01:12:23,673 --> 01:12:25,339
AND I WANT IT.

1441
01:12:25,408 --> 01:12:27,808
OH!     WE CAN SIGN THE PAPERS  
        HERE TONIGHT...

1442
01:12:27,877 --> 01:12:29,177
IN 5 MINUTES,           
        AND IN 3 MONTHS,

1443
01:12:29,245 --> 01:12:31,212
WE COULD OPEN IN PARIS,

1444
01:12:31,281 --> 01:12:32,613
BERLIN, MILAN.

1445
01:12:32,682 --> 01:12:33,614
UHH.

1446
01:12:33,683 --> 01:12:34,982
ALL RIGHT,          
            WHEREVER YOU WANT.

1447
01:12:35,051 --> 01:12:35,983
JAPAN.

1448
01:12:36,052 --> 01:12:37,452
AHH.

1449
01:12:37,520 --> 01:12:38,386
AHH.

1450
01:12:40,090 --> 01:12:41,189
AHH...

1451
01:12:47,830 --> 01:12:48,696
PAPA.

1452
01:12:50,133 --> 01:12:51,165
AH.

1453
01:12:53,769 --> 01:12:55,002
OH.

1454
01:12:57,474 --> 01:12:58,573
YES.

1455
01:12:58,641 --> 01:13:00,475
I TAUGHT YOU TO READ,

1456
01:13:00,543 --> 01:13:03,411
AND LIFE WAS            
        YOUR ONLY SCHOOL.

1457
01:13:03,480 --> 01:13:04,912
DON'T YOU WORRY.

1458
01:13:04,981 --> 01:13:07,448
TOMORROW, I WILL TALK   
        TO PONTIUS PILATE

1459
01:13:07,517 --> 01:13:09,783
WITH MORE LUCK          
        THAN THE OTHER.

1460
01:13:09,852 --> 01:13:11,252
I HOPE SO.

1461
01:13:11,321 --> 01:13:14,188
AHH. YOU GO, HMM?

1462
01:13:14,257 --> 01:13:15,423
REST.

1463
01:13:15,492 --> 01:13:17,291
DO YOUR WORK.

1464
01:13:17,360 --> 01:13:18,859
ALLOW ME TO DO MINE.

1465
01:13:18,928 --> 01:13:20,728
YOU GO TO TUCCIO.

1466
01:13:20,796 --> 01:13:23,931
HE NEEDS YOU NOW, HMM?

1467
01:13:23,999 --> 01:13:25,433
WHAT IS YOUR HURRY?

1468
01:13:25,502 --> 01:13:27,401
WHAT HAS HAPPENED   
            IS BUT THE PROLOGUE.

1469
01:13:27,470 --> 01:13:28,336
LOOK.

1470
01:13:29,506 --> 01:13:31,239
LOOK AT ME.

1471
01:13:31,307 --> 01:13:32,773
THAT...

1472
01:13:32,842 --> 01:13:33,807
IS YOURS.

1473
01:13:34,944 --> 01:13:35,943
OH, NO.

1474
01:13:36,012 --> 01:13:37,311
OH, YES.

1475
01:13:37,380 --> 01:13:38,979
I NEED MEANING  
                IN MY LIFE.

1476
01:13:39,048 --> 01:13:40,881
GIVE ME MEANING.

1477
01:13:43,853 --> 01:13:45,719
THIS MOMENT--

1478
01:13:45,788 --> 01:13:48,156
IT WILL NEVER RETURN.

1479
01:13:51,827 --> 01:13:53,827
[LAUGHS]

1480
01:13:53,896 --> 01:13:55,296
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

1481
01:13:56,566 --> 01:13:58,266
BACK TO HER?

1482
01:13:58,334 --> 01:14:00,434
WHAT, TO HOLD       
            EACH OTHER'S HANDS?

1483
01:14:01,804 --> 01:14:02,737
TRY TO BEHAVE           
        LIKE A GENTLEMAN,

1484
01:14:02,805 --> 01:14:04,071
SINCE NOTHING COULD     
        EVER CONVINCE YOU

1485
01:14:04,139 --> 01:14:05,055
TO BEHAVE LIKE A LADY.

1486
01:14:05,124 --> 01:14:06,807
YOU BEAST!

1487
01:14:06,876 --> 01:14:08,743
AAH!

1488
01:14:08,811 --> 01:14:10,043
YOU LIKE THAT, HUH?

1489
01:14:10,112 --> 01:14:11,445
I WEEP. I WEEP,                 
THAT'S ALL,

1490
01:14:11,514 --> 01:14:13,347
AND WEEPING MAKES ME UGLY.

1491
01:14:13,416 --> 01:14:15,616
THE PERFORMANCE OVER?

1492
01:14:15,685 --> 01:14:16,650
NO.

1493
01:14:16,719 --> 01:14:18,151
NO. I NEVER                     
STOP ACTING.

1494
01:14:18,220 --> 01:14:20,153
I HAVE ALWAYS ACTED--

1495
01:14:20,222 --> 01:14:22,523
ALWAYS AND EVERYWHERE.

1496
01:14:22,592 --> 01:14:24,258
I AM MY OWN DOUBLE.

1497
01:14:24,326 --> 01:14:26,694
I ACT IN THE MORNING            
WHEN I LOOK IN THE MIRROR.

1498
01:14:26,763 --> 01:14:29,329
I ACT IN RESTAURANTS          
  WHEN I ASK FOR MORE BREAD.

1499
01:14:29,399 --> 01:14:31,832
I ACT WHEN I TELL MY MOTHER     
THAT I LOVE HER.

1500
01:14:31,901 --> 01:14:35,002
I LOVE--I ADORE                 
MY PROFESSION.

1501
01:14:35,070 --> 01:14:36,604
I SERVE IT CONSTANTLY.

1502
01:14:38,908 --> 01:14:40,841
IT IS MY ONLY FRIEND.

1503
01:14:42,011 --> 01:14:43,711
I'M GOING.

1504
01:14:43,780 --> 01:14:45,679
NO! NO.

1505
01:14:45,748 --> 01:14:48,115
IT'S A SLENDER CURTAIN          
BETWEEN THEATER AND LIFE.

1506
01:14:50,152 --> 01:14:52,686
IN THE NAME         
            OF ALL THAT'S REAL,

1507
01:14:52,755 --> 01:14:53,687
I'M GOING.

1508
01:14:53,756 --> 01:14:55,355
NO! NO! NO!

1509
01:14:57,426 --> 01:15:00,193
OH, YES, CARESS ME.

1510
01:15:00,262 --> 01:15:02,730
OH, I LOVE IT     
              WHEN YOU CARESS M.

1511
01:15:02,799 --> 01:15:04,231
A KISS.

1512
01:15:04,300 --> 01:15:05,599
OHH.

1513
01:15:05,668 --> 01:15:07,334
[SNORTS]

1514
01:15:12,575 --> 01:15:13,774
[WHEEZES]

1515
01:15:13,843 --> 01:15:15,008
OHH!

1516
01:15:15,077 --> 01:15:18,512
[SINGING ALONG]         
    ♪♪ LIFE BY THY SIDE ♪♪

1517
01:15:18,581 --> 01:15:24,051
♪♪ IT IS TIME ♪♪

1518
01:15:24,119 --> 01:15:25,252
♪♪ LOVE... ♪♪

1519
01:15:25,321 --> 01:15:27,287
DON'T MOVE,                 
    OR I'LL KILL YOU!

1520
01:15:27,356 --> 01:15:29,089
I'LL KILL YOU!

1521
01:15:29,158 --> 01:15:30,491
I'LL KILL YOU.

1522
01:15:30,560 --> 01:15:33,026
Passerby: STOP, THIEVES!

1523
01:15:33,095 --> 01:15:34,595
STOP! STOP THAT!

1524
01:15:38,568 --> 01:15:40,067
STOP IT!

1525
01:15:40,135 --> 01:15:42,202
GET AWAY FROM ME!   
            I'LL KILL HIM!

1526
01:15:42,271 --> 01:15:43,554
NO, NO, DON'T DO IT.

1527
01:15:43,623 --> 01:15:46,774
OH, I'M FLYING, BEPPO.

1528
01:15:46,843 --> 01:15:49,376
<i>  ESTO VOLANDO!</i>

1529
01:15:49,445 --> 01:15:52,746
♪♪ OH ♪♪

1530
01:15:52,815 --> 01:15:55,582
NOW YOU'RE          
            GOING TO GET IT.

1531
01:15:55,651 --> 01:15:58,652
STOP HIM!       
                PLEASE! PLEASE!

1532
01:15:58,721 --> 01:15:59,787
PLEASE!

1533
01:17:05,187 --> 01:17:07,087
THIS IS WHAT                    
I'VE ALWAYS WISHED...

1534
01:17:09,725 --> 01:17:12,760
NOTHING ON YOUR MIND            
BUT PIERO, PIERO, PIERO.

1535
01:17:17,600 --> 01:17:20,333
MY ONLY WISH...

1536
01:17:20,403 --> 01:17:22,669
THE WISH OF                     
A SMALL-PART PLAYER

1537
01:17:22,738 --> 01:17:26,306
WHO LONGS TO PLAY THE LEAD      
FOR ONCE IN HIS LIFE.

1538
01:17:30,112 --> 01:17:31,678
PLAY WITH ME, MY LOVE...

1539
01:17:34,149 --> 01:17:37,350
THE WORDS I WAS NEVER ABLE      
TO HEAR YOU SAY.

1540
01:17:38,687 --> 01:17:42,256
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT LIKE    
    SOME BREAKFAST, MY DARLING.

1541
01:17:42,325 --> 01:17:44,825
HOW THOUGHTFUL.

1542
01:17:44,893 --> 01:17:46,227
SOME TEA.

1543
01:17:46,295 --> 01:17:48,295
WHY, YES.

1544
01:17:48,364 --> 01:17:49,796
THANK YOU.

1545
01:17:49,865 --> 01:17:53,834
YOU LOOK PARTICULARLY   
        ALIVE THIS MORNING.

1546
01:17:53,902 --> 01:17:56,570
THANK YOU.                      
SO DO YOU.

1547
01:17:56,639 --> 01:17:58,138
I FEEL ALIVE.

1548
01:17:58,207 --> 01:18:01,709
I FEEL GLAD         
            TO BE ALIVE.

1549
01:18:01,777 --> 01:18:03,877
SO AM I.

1550
01:18:03,946 --> 01:18:05,946
MY KUMQUAT.

1551
01:18:07,450 --> 01:18:09,450
SOME MELON PERHAPS?

1552
01:18:09,518 --> 01:18:11,184
PLEASE.

1553
01:18:11,254 --> 01:18:12,553
[CHUCKLES]

1554
01:18:15,625 --> 01:18:18,525
WE LIVE IN A DRAMA...

1555
01:18:19,795 --> 01:18:22,496
MY BUTTERCUP.

1556
01:18:22,565 --> 01:18:25,031
AND THAT IS OUR TRIUMPH.

1557
01:18:25,100 --> 01:18:28,101
THE TRIUMPH             
        OF OUR IMAGINATION.

1558
01:18:31,173 --> 01:18:34,575
DANCE WITH ME, SALOME.      
    DANCE WITH ME, SALOME.

1559
01:18:34,644 --> 01:18:35,809
OH, MY!

1560
01:18:35,878 --> 01:18:36,810
WHAT?!

1561
01:18:39,682 --> 01:18:41,448
STOP! STOP, BEPPO!

1562
01:18:43,152 --> 01:18:44,084
[SIGHS]

1563
01:18:44,153 --> 01:18:46,253
IT'S BEEN A ROUGH   
            NIGHT ALL AROUND.

1564
01:18:46,322 --> 01:18:48,188
[HORSE WHINNIES,
                DOG BARKING]

1565
01:18:48,257 --> 01:18:49,290
HEY.

1566
01:18:50,793 --> 01:18:53,827
WHAT DO YOU THINK   
            YOU'RE DOING...

1567
01:18:53,896 --> 01:18:56,163
IN THE MIDDLE       
            OF THE NIGHT?

1568
01:18:56,231 --> 01:18:57,498
[WHINNIES]

1569
01:18:58,901 --> 01:19:02,586
Beppo: WHERE HAS HE BEEN,   
        THAT WHOREMONGER?

1570
01:19:02,655 --> 01:19:04,538
[RACHEL HUMMING]

1571
01:19:12,948 --> 01:19:14,181
[KNOCK KNOCK]

1572
01:19:14,249 --> 01:19:15,416
COME IN.

1573
01:19:16,852 --> 01:19:18,885
WHAT NEWS?

1574
01:19:18,954 --> 01:19:20,621
GOOD NEWS.

1575
01:19:20,690 --> 01:19:22,723
<i>  ILLUMINATA'S</i>                  
  NOT CANCELED.

1576
01:19:22,792 --> 01:19:24,625
SOMETHING HAS HAPPENED          
SOMEWHERE,

1577
01:19:24,694 --> 01:19:27,428
THOUGH I REMAIN,                
AS ALWAYS, IN THE DARK.

1578
01:19:27,496 --> 01:19:28,762
WE'RE DOING     
                TUCCIO'S PLAY?

1579
01:19:28,831 --> 01:19:29,963
YES, IT'S BEEN DECIDED.

1580
01:19:30,032 --> 01:19:31,532
TONIGHT THE CRITICS             
ARE RETURNING,

1581
01:19:31,584 --> 01:19:32,933
EVEN BEVALAQUA.

1582
01:19:34,370 --> 01:19:35,969
HOW'D YOU SLEEP,
                MY TUCCIO?

1583
01:19:36,038 --> 01:19:36,937
WELL ENOUGH.

1584
01:19:40,108 --> 01:19:42,108
MMM.

1585
01:19:42,177 --> 01:19:44,144
FEELS GOOD                      
TO CLEAN YOURSELF, HUH?

1586
01:19:44,213 --> 01:19:46,413
WELL, I'LL SEE YOU              
AT THE REHEARSAL.

1587
01:19:46,482 --> 01:19:47,414
WHAT REHEARSAL?

1588
01:19:47,483 --> 01:19:48,415
FOR YOUR PLAY.

1589
01:19:48,484 --> 01:19:50,417
I HAVE NO PLAY.     
            IT'S CANCELED.

1590
01:19:50,486 --> 01:19:52,152
NO PLAY?                        
THEN NO REHEARSAL.

1591
01:19:52,221 --> 01:19:54,154
BUT YOU JUST SAID   
            THAT I--

1592
01:19:54,223 --> 01:19:58,091
I DID HEAR SOMETHING, YES,      
BUT IT MUST BE A LIE...

1593
01:19:58,160 --> 01:19:59,727
LIKE MANY THINGS HERE.

1594
01:20:01,063 --> 01:20:02,329
HOW DID YOU SLEEP?

1595
01:20:02,398 --> 01:20:04,264
I SLEPT FINE.           
        DIDN'T YOU ASK ME THAT?

1596
01:20:04,333 --> 01:20:05,666
HE LIES                         
RIGHT TO MY EYES.

1597
01:20:05,735 --> 01:20:07,100
WHAT IS GOING ON HERE?

1598
01:20:07,169 --> 01:20:09,370
THAT'S WHAT I'D                 
LIKE TO KNOW.

1599
01:20:09,438 --> 01:20:11,672
RACHEL STRUCK A DEAL            
WITH PALLENCHIO.

1600
01:20:11,741 --> 01:20:14,241
A DEAL?

1601
01:20:14,309 --> 01:20:15,942
I THOUGHT           
            WE WERE CLOSED.

1602
01:20:16,011 --> 01:20:17,711
YOU THOUGHT?                    
YOU THOUGHT!

1603
01:20:17,780 --> 01:20:19,847
OUR RACHEL WOULD NOT            
DO THEIR IBSEN

1604
01:20:19,915 --> 01:20:22,449
IF THEY REFUSED                 
THIS CHANCE TO YOU.

1605
01:20:22,518 --> 01:20:25,018
WE HAVE TODAY                   
TO FIX THE PLAY.

1606
01:20:25,087 --> 01:20:27,554
YOU PERFORM TONIGHT.

1607
01:20:27,623 --> 01:20:30,190
IF THEY LIKE IT, PFFT,          
WE HAVE OUR RUN.

1608
01:20:30,259 --> 01:20:32,959
RACHEL DID THIS?

1609
01:20:33,028 --> 01:20:35,028
THAT TRAITOR.

1610
01:20:38,401 --> 01:20:40,200
YOU MEAN HIM    
                AND CELIMENE?

1611
01:20:40,268 --> 01:20:41,702
TUCCIO AND CELIMENE?

1612
01:20:41,770 --> 01:20:42,736
HAVE YOU HEARD?

1613
01:20:42,804 --> 01:20:44,070
ALWAYS THE LAST 
                TO KNOW.

1614
01:20:44,139 --> 01:20:45,171
TUCCIO'S IN             
        WITH CELIMENE.

1615
01:20:45,241 --> 01:20:46,440
WHO HASN'T BEEN IN  
            WITH CELIMENE?

1616
01:20:46,508 --> 01:20:47,507
YOU'VE BEEN IN HER?

1617
01:20:47,576 --> 01:20:49,243
SHE SAW MY RIGID BONE.

1618
01:20:49,311 --> 01:20:50,277
I LIVE THROUGH YOU,             
DOMINIQUE.

1619
01:20:50,346 --> 01:20:51,712
DON'T YOU KNOW      
            WHAT THIS MEANS?

1620
01:20:51,780 --> 01:20:53,413
IF HE'S CAPABLE OF  
            SLEEPING WITH HER--

1621
01:20:53,482 --> 01:20:54,715
BUT ARE YOU SURE            
    HE'S SLEEPING WITH HER?

1622
01:20:54,783 --> 01:20:57,083
THEN HE'S CAPABLE OF
            TOURING WITH HER.

1623
01:20:57,153 --> 01:20:58,084
TOURING     
                    WITH HER?

1624
01:20:58,153 --> 01:20:59,219
IN WHAT?                        
NOT THIS PLAY?

1625
01:20:59,287 --> 01:21:01,121
NO, BUT WHAT ABOUT      
        HIS NEXT PLAY, NEW PLAY?

1626
01:21:01,190 --> 01:21:03,123
HIS NEW PLAY? THE ONE       
    HE'S WRITING FOR ME?

1627
01:21:03,191 --> 01:21:04,791
IN PARIS.

1628
01:21:04,861 --> 01:21:06,593
PARIS?

1629
01:21:06,662 --> 01:21:09,429
YES. HIS NEW PLAY IN PARIS      
WITH THAT BITCH CELIMENE!

1630
01:21:09,498 --> 01:21:11,598
WHAT ABOUT YOU?         
        WHAT ABOUT THE COMPANY?

1631
01:21:11,667 --> 01:21:12,799
WE'RE OUT.      
                THAT'S PLAIN.

1632
01:21:12,868 --> 01:21:14,234
HE INTENDS IT                   
FOR NONE OF US.

1633
01:21:14,303 --> 01:21:16,270
NONE?

1634
01:21:16,338 --> 01:21:18,238
[MUTTERS]

1635
01:21:18,307 --> 01:21:19,339
NOT ME?

1636
01:21:23,345 --> 01:21:24,745
NOT ME?

1637
01:21:24,813 --> 01:21:26,780
NO. NOT YOU.

1638
01:21:30,051 --> 01:21:31,184
BUT...

1639
01:21:32,721 --> 01:21:34,888
THAT--THAT--THAT PART,      
    THAT WAS...

1640
01:21:34,956 --> 01:21:37,591
BUT IT WAS PERFECT          
    FOR ME, WASN'T IT?

1641
01:21:37,660 --> 01:21:38,525
YES.

1642
01:21:40,228 --> 01:21:41,428
IT HAD ALL MY...

1643
01:21:44,099 --> 01:21:46,933
MY GOD,                     
    IF THIS IS TRUE...

1644
01:21:47,002 --> 01:21:48,868
THEN THAT MAN               
    IS A TRAITOR.

1645
01:22:01,283 --> 01:22:03,149
[BOYS PLAYING]

1646
01:22:10,492 --> 01:22:12,058
PARIS, WITHOUT ME?

1647
01:22:12,127 --> 01:22:13,159
HMPH.

1648
01:22:22,671 --> 01:22:25,339
IT'S FUNNY              
    HOW I FEEL REAL NOW.

1649
01:22:25,407 --> 01:22:27,073
I FEEL REAL.

1650
01:22:27,142 --> 01:22:29,643
I FEEL FIT TO RESPOND       
        NOT AS AN ACTOR,

1651
01:22:29,712 --> 01:22:31,878
NO, BUT AS A MAN,       
        PUT IT SIMPLY.

1652
01:22:31,947 --> 01:22:34,481
YOU BASTARD!

1653
01:22:34,550 --> 01:22:36,149
MMM!

1654
01:22:36,218 --> 01:22:37,618
MAN TO MAN.

1655
01:22:37,686 --> 01:22:42,055
YOU SLIMY DUPLICITOUS       
        LITTLE SHIT!

1656
01:22:42,124 --> 01:22:44,558
HMPH. HERE!

1657
01:22:44,627 --> 01:22:46,092
IN--IN--IN LIFE!

1658
01:22:46,161 --> 01:22:47,427
YOU BASTARD!

1659
01:22:47,496 --> 01:22:48,995
[DOOR CLOSES]

1660
01:22:49,064 --> 01:22:50,830
DO I INTERRUPT?

1661
01:22:50,899 --> 01:22:52,499
NO, NOT AT ALL, 
                DARLING.

1662
01:22:52,568 --> 01:22:54,968
THIS ENDING.                    
TUCCIO'S ENDING.

1663
01:22:55,036 --> 01:22:56,236
YES, FROM WHERE,

1664
01:22:56,305 --> 01:22:58,204
"YOU LIED TO ME,    
            AND I KNOW IT"?

1665
01:22:58,274 --> 01:22:59,473
YES, YES,                       
"YOU LIED TO ME..."

1666
01:22:59,541 --> 01:23:01,040
WE'RE STILL                     
ONE STEP AWAY.

1667
01:23:01,109 --> 01:23:02,041
YES, I KNOW.

1668
01:23:02,110 --> 01:23:03,577
DO YOU THINK IT                 
TRUTHFUL?

1669
01:23:03,646 --> 01:23:06,313
TRUTHFUL?

1670
01:23:06,382 --> 01:23:08,649
WELL, I DID,        
            BUT NOW I DON'T.

1671
01:23:08,717 --> 01:23:10,116
SOMETHING'S MISSING.

1672
01:23:10,185 --> 01:23:11,818
DARLING, WHY DON'T--    
        SHALL WE TRY SOMETHING?

1673
01:23:11,887 --> 01:23:13,487
SHALL WE JUST REHEARSE  
        A LITTLE?

1674
01:23:13,555 --> 01:23:15,922
UM, LET'S TRY THIS.

1675
01:23:15,991 --> 01:23:19,593
HIS NEXT PLAY           
        WILL BE DONE IN PARIS.

1676
01:23:19,662 --> 01:23:20,927
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

1677
01:23:20,996 --> 01:23:25,632
HIS NEXT PLAY, FOR HER, 
        IN PARIS.

