WHAT AM I TO DO?

1685
01:23:42,150 --> 01:23:43,116
DESERT HIM!

1686
01:23:43,185 --> 01:23:44,117
I CANNOT.

1687
01:23:44,186 --> 01:23:45,102
YOU FOOL.       
                WHY NOT?

1688
01:23:45,171 --> 01:23:47,354
YOU ASK WHY?                    
BECAUSE I LOVE HIM.

1689
01:23:47,423 --> 01:23:48,355
AGAIN.

1690
01:23:48,424 --> 01:23:49,356
DESERT ME.

1691
01:23:49,425 --> 01:23:50,390
I CANNOT.

1692
01:23:50,459 --> 01:23:51,758
YOU FOOL!   
                    WHY NOT?

1693
01:23:51,827 --> 01:23:54,511
YOU ASK WHY?                    
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU.

1694
01:23:54,580 --> 01:23:55,729
IT'S GOOD.              
        IT'S BETTER, ISN'T IT?

1695
01:23:55,798 --> 01:23:57,130
CAN WE GO ON?                   
                    CERTAINLY.

1696
01:23:57,199 --> 01:24:00,066
YOU WANT ME TO STAY IN  
        THE PLAY, OR SHALL I--

1697
01:24:00,119 --> 01:24:01,401
NO, NO.                     
    LET'S STAY OUTSIDE.

1698
01:24:01,470 --> 01:24:04,237
OH, I SHOULDN'T HAVE            
SAID ANYTHING TO YOU.

1699
01:24:04,306 --> 01:24:06,573
WE MUST NOT BREATHE         
    A WORD OF THIS TO RACHEL.

1700
01:24:06,642 --> 01:24:08,107
IT WOULD BREAK HER HEART    
    TO HEAR IT.

1701
01:24:08,176 --> 01:24:10,310
SHE MUST FIND OUT               
SOONER OR LATER.

1702
01:24:10,379 --> 01:24:12,479
WELL, THEN LET HER      
        FIND OUT LATER.

1703
01:24:12,548 --> 01:24:15,349
ORLANDINI, DEATH ITSELF 
        WOULD NOT SILENCE YOU.

1704
01:24:15,417 --> 01:24:16,817
OH, YOU LIE.                    
DEATH COULD.

1705
01:24:16,885 --> 01:24:19,252
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

1706
01:24:19,321 --> 01:24:21,187
[BOYS PLAYING]

1707
01:24:27,295 --> 01:24:29,529
YOU WON'T TELL ANYONE?

1708
01:24:29,598 --> 01:24:30,831
YOU HAVE MY WORD.

1709
01:24:32,668 --> 01:24:34,300
TUCCIO WILL DO                  
HIS NEXT PLAY...

1710
01:24:34,370 --> 01:24:35,335
IN PARIS!

1711
01:24:35,403 --> 01:24:36,770
WITH CELIMENE!

1712
01:24:47,516 --> 01:24:49,449
YOU MADE YOUR POINT             
ABOUT PARIS.

1713
01:24:49,518 --> 01:24:51,351
WHY DO YOU                      
GO BACK TO IT?

1714
01:24:51,420 --> 01:24:53,787
OH, I DON'T KNOW.       
        NO REASON, REALLY.

1715
01:24:53,856 --> 01:24:56,556
PERHAPS                         
YOU KNOW SOMETHING?

1716
01:24:56,625 --> 01:24:58,191
[LAUGHING]

1717
01:24:58,260 --> 01:25:01,194
NO. RACHEL, NO.

1718
01:25:01,263 --> 01:25:03,329
I'M JUST MAKING IT UP.  
        I'M PLAYING.

1719
01:25:03,399 --> 01:25:07,200
I MEAN, THINK ABOUT IT. 
        IT'S A RIDICULOUS IDEA.

1720
01:25:07,269 --> 01:25:10,537
BECAUSE HE IS CAPABLE OF        
JUST SUCH INFAMOUS BEHAVIOR.

1721
01:25:10,606 --> 01:25:12,272
YES,                
            HE IS VERY CAPABLE.

1722
01:25:15,076 --> 01:25:16,309
SO PARIS                        
HAS COMMITTED?

1723
01:25:16,378 --> 01:25:17,277
MMM.

1724
01:25:19,081 --> 01:25:20,113
TUCCIO IN PARIS?

1725
01:25:20,181 --> 01:25:21,281
THEY'RE RAVING          
        ABOUT HIM.

1726
01:25:21,350 --> 01:25:22,382
HE'S THE WRITER         
        OF THE MOMENT,

1727
01:25:22,451 --> 01:25:24,284
AND HE SLIPPED          
        RIGHT THROUGH OUR HANDS.

1728
01:25:24,353 --> 01:25:25,685
YOU LIKED HIM                   
EVEN LESS THAN I.

1729
01:25:25,754 --> 01:25:27,420
I? HE NEEDED        
            TO BE EDITED.

1730
01:25:27,489 --> 01:25:28,788
WILL YOU STOP       
            SHAKING YOUR LEG?

1731
01:25:28,857 --> 01:25:30,457
I'M NOT SHAKING.                
YOU'RE SHAKING.

1732
01:25:30,525 --> 01:25:32,058
I'M NOT SHAKING.

1733
01:25:32,127 --> 01:25:34,093
IT WAS YOU WHO      
            DOUBTED HIS GENIUS.

1734
01:25:34,162 --> 01:25:35,662
MY FAITH IN HIM     
            NEVER WAVERED.

1735
01:25:35,731 --> 01:25:36,996
THAT'S ALL          
            HE EVER NEEDED

1736
01:25:37,065 --> 01:25:38,498
WAS TO BE SURROUNDED
            BY PEOPLE

1737
01:25:38,567 --> 01:25:40,133
WHO HAD FAITH       
            IN HIM.

1738
01:25:40,201 --> 01:25:41,134
FUCK PARIS.

1739
01:25:41,202 --> 01:25:42,702
THEY'VE BEEN WRONG BEFORE,      
YOU KNOW.

1740
01:25:42,771 --> 01:25:44,404
FUCK PARIS?             
        NOBODY FUCKS PARIS!

1741
01:25:44,473 --> 01:25:46,640
YOU FUCK PARIS, YOU OPEN
        THE DOORS TO BARBARIANS.

1742
01:25:46,708 --> 01:25:48,841
YOU BANISH            
          HONEST FEELING,

1743
01:25:48,910 --> 01:25:50,510
PROUD LANGUAGE,         
        CREPES.

1744
01:25:50,579 --> 01:25:52,445
YOU--YOU BANISH LOVE!

1745
01:26:04,593 --> 01:26:05,759
[BOYS LAUGHING]

1746
01:26:05,827 --> 01:26:07,827
[WOODEN SWORDS BANGING]

1747
01:26:07,896 --> 01:26:08,995
HO HO!                          
                HO HO!

1748
01:26:09,063 --> 01:26:09,996
HUH!

1749
01:26:10,064 --> 01:26:12,699
HELP ME, PIERO! 
                HELP ME!

1750
01:26:12,768 --> 01:26:15,635
HE CAN'T. I KILLED HIM      
    WITH THIS SWORD.

1751
01:26:15,704 --> 01:26:16,636
OH.

1752
01:26:16,705 --> 01:26:19,172
VIKINGS.                        
THE VIKING HAS ARRIVED.

1753
01:26:19,240 --> 01:26:21,040
VIKINGS!                
                        VIKINGS!

1754
01:26:24,012 --> 01:26:25,578
I HATE VIKINGS.

1755
01:26:27,683 --> 01:26:29,115
OF COURSE, SAY NOTHING,

1756
01:26:29,184 --> 01:26:31,184
NOR SHOW IN ANY WAY             
THAT WE'VE HEARD A THING,

1757
01:26:31,252 --> 01:26:33,186
NOR BELIEVE ONE WORD OF IT.

1758
01:26:33,254 --> 01:26:35,188
OH, NO,                 
        WHICH DO YOU PREFER--

1759
01:26:35,256 --> 01:26:37,223
THAT WE HAVEN'T         
        HEARD A THING

1760
01:26:37,292 --> 01:26:39,292
OR WE DON'T BELIEVE     
        WHAT WE DID HEAR?

1761
01:26:39,361 --> 01:26:40,827
I THINK BOTH.

1762
01:26:40,895 --> 01:26:42,629
I CAN'T. THAT'S VERY    
        DIFFICULT FOR ME--

1763
01:26:42,698 --> 01:26:46,098
NOT TO BELIEVE SOMETHING
        I HAVEN'T HEARD.

1764
01:26:46,167 --> 01:26:48,368
YOU'RE RIGHT. THE THING         
HAS ME IN ITS GRIP ALREADY.

1765
01:26:48,437 --> 01:26:50,002
I THINK--               
                    FORGIVE ME.

1766
01:26:52,241 --> 01:26:53,139
HA.

1767
01:26:54,309 --> 01:26:56,409
I ASK AGAIN, FORGIVE.

1768
01:27:01,183 --> 01:27:03,583
IS THERE        
                SOMETHING WRONG?

1769
01:27:03,652 --> 01:27:05,485
NOT WITH ME.        
            WITH YOU?

1770
01:27:05,554 --> 01:27:08,154
NO. NOT THAT    
                I'M AWARE OF.

1771
01:27:08,223 --> 01:27:11,190
AWARE? WHAT MAKES YOU THINK 
    YOU HAVE TO BE AWARE?

1772
01:27:11,259 --> 01:27:12,325
HUH.

1773
01:27:12,394 --> 01:27:15,194
THINGS HAPPEN EVERY DAY     
    THAT NO ONE IS AWARE OF.

1774
01:27:15,264 --> 01:27:17,964
VERY TRUE, ISN'T IT?    
        IT'S TRUE, VERY TRUE.

1775
01:27:18,032 --> 01:27:20,667
THINGS HAPPEN ON THE OCEAN      
WHERE NO ONE IS

1776
01:27:20,736 --> 01:27:25,338
AND IN ANTARCTICA             
  WHERE IT'S TOO COLD TO BE.

1777
01:27:25,407 --> 01:27:27,974
YES, THINGS HAPPEN              
EVEN THERE,

1778
01:27:28,042 --> 01:27:31,378
HAVE BEEN HAPPENING THERE       
FOR YEARS,

1779
01:27:31,446 --> 01:27:34,614
WHICH NO ONE IS AWARE OF.

1780
01:27:34,683 --> 01:27:36,549
YET THEY HAPPEN,

1781
01:27:36,618 --> 01:27:38,751
GO ON HAPPENING,

1782
01:27:38,820 --> 01:27:39,819
AWARE OR NOT.

1783
01:27:41,890 --> 01:27:44,057
[BOYS PLAYING,                  
BELL TOLLING]

1784
01:27:44,125 --> 01:27:45,725
OH, MY!

1785
01:27:45,794 --> 01:27:47,727
OH, MY LOVE!

1786
01:27:47,796 --> 01:27:50,063
MY LOVE!

1787
01:27:50,131 --> 01:27:51,665
MY LOVE!

1788
01:27:51,733 --> 01:27:52,732
MARTA!

1789
01:27:52,801 --> 01:27:54,967
I CAN LIVE MY LIFE      
        WITHOUT YOU.

1790
01:27:55,036 --> 01:27:56,002
AND THERE'S             
        SOMETHING MORE.

1791
01:27:56,071 --> 01:27:57,671
BY ALL MEANS,       
            LET ME HEAR IT.

1792
01:27:57,739 --> 01:27:59,472
I CAN'T STAND YOU.

1793
01:27:59,541 --> 01:28:01,741
MY EUROPEAN TOUR                
WHEN I DID YOUR PLAYS?

1794
01:28:01,810 --> 01:28:04,143
ALL THOSE THEATERS I TOLD YOU   
WERE FULL...WERE NOT.

1795
01:28:04,213 --> 01:28:06,646
FOR THE FIRST TIME              
ON A TOUR OF MINE,

1796
01:28:06,715 --> 01:28:08,081
THEY WERE NOT FULL.

1797
01:28:08,149 --> 01:28:09,216
YOUR ROYALTIES--

1798
01:28:09,284 --> 01:28:13,553
I SENT YOU EVERY CENT           
ACCORDING TO FULL HOUSES.

1799
01:28:13,622 --> 01:28:16,856
I MADE UP THE DIFFERENCE        
OUT OF MY OWN POCKET.

1800
01:28:16,925 --> 01:28:17,857
YOU SHOULD'VE TOLD ME.

1801
01:28:17,926 --> 01:28:19,459
YES,                            
THAT IS WHAT YOU SAY.

1802
01:28:19,528 --> 01:28:22,295
BECAUSE YOU'VE NEVER            
LOVED ANYONE.

1803
01:28:22,364 --> 01:28:25,765
I COULDN'T BEAR YOU TO THINK    
WE WEREN'T SELLING OUT.

1804
01:28:25,834 --> 01:28:29,402
HOW I'VE LOVED YOU,             
AND WHAT A FOOL I'VE BEEN!

1805
01:28:29,471 --> 01:28:31,170
JUST GO ON! GO AWAY!            
GET OUT!

1806
01:28:31,240 --> 01:28:33,673
NO, NO, NO.         
            I WON'T GET OUT.

1807
01:28:33,742 --> 01:28:34,674
GET OUT!

1808
01:28:34,743 --> 01:28:36,008
I LIKE IT HERE.

1809
01:28:36,077 --> 01:28:37,711
YOU DON'T LIKE IT HERE.

1810
01:28:37,779 --> 01:28:39,212
WELL, IF YOU MEAN   
            THIS THEATER--

1811
01:28:39,281 --> 01:28:40,714
YES, I MEAN                     
THIS THEATER, YES.

1812
01:28:40,782 --> 01:28:43,216
YES, THAT'S SO.         
        I DO NOT LIKE IT HERE.

1813
01:28:43,285 --> 01:28:45,418
HA. AT LEAST                    
THAT'S NOT ANOTHER LIE.

1814
01:28:45,487 --> 01:28:46,986
SINCE WHEN IS               
    ALL I SAY A LIE?

1815
01:28:47,055 --> 01:28:48,321
SINCE THE DAY WE MET.

1816
01:28:48,390 --> 01:28:49,689
NO. THERE YOU ARE WRONG.

1817
01:28:49,758 --> 01:28:52,525
THE DAY WE MET,                 
EVERYTHING I SAID WAS TRUE.

1818
01:28:52,594 --> 01:28:56,296
I STARTED LYING ON              
THE SECOND DAY...AT DAWN.

1819
01:28:56,365 --> 01:28:58,131
AS IF YOU               
        REMEMBER THAT DAY

1820
01:28:58,199 --> 01:28:59,799
OR ANY DAY WITH ME.

1821
01:28:59,868 --> 01:29:01,401
WELL, SOME ARE LESS CLEAR       
THAN OTHERS,

1822
01:29:01,470 --> 01:29:04,070
BUT THE FIRST DAY               
WAS THE DAY...

1823
01:29:04,139 --> 01:29:05,272
OF OUR FIRST KISS,

1824
01:29:05,340 --> 01:29:07,474
AND THAT DAY...

1825
01:29:07,542 --> 01:29:08,675
I REMEMBER...

1826
01:29:10,512 --> 01:29:13,680
HOW PALE YOU WERE               
AND FLUSHED BY TURN...

1827
01:29:16,117 --> 01:29:19,386
AND HOW I FOUGHT TO KEEP        
SOME SPACE BETWEEN US,

1828
01:29:19,454 --> 01:29:22,088
FOR I DID NOT                   
WANT TO LOVE YOU

1829
01:29:22,157 --> 01:29:25,392
AS DEEPLY                       
AS I KNEW I WOULD.

1830
01:29:28,530 --> 01:29:30,096
OH, TUCCIO.

1831
01:29:32,066 --> 01:29:34,033
HOW CAN YOU         
            SAY SUCH THINGS

1832
01:29:34,102 --> 01:29:37,337
AND BE SO HORRIBLE  
            TO ME?

1833
01:29:37,406 --> 01:29:42,842
MY BEING HORRIBLE TO YOU,       
RACHEL, IS PART OF MY LOVE.

1834
01:29:42,911 --> 01:29:45,211
I THOUGHT YOU KNEW THAT.

1835
01:29:45,280 --> 01:29:46,646
WHERE'S TUCCIO?

1836
01:29:46,715 --> 01:29:47,914
THERE.

1837
01:29:47,983 --> 01:29:50,750
HO HO! SO, PARIS?

1838
01:29:50,819 --> 01:29:51,784
PARIS?

1839
01:29:51,854 --> 01:29:52,986
WHAT'S PARIS?

1840
01:29:53,055 --> 01:29:54,687
A CITY                  
        FULL OF TARTS.

1841
01:29:54,756 --> 01:29:56,789
WITH CELIMENE.                  
YOU'RE COMMITTED.

1842
01:29:56,859 --> 01:29:58,491
TARTS                       
    AND CHEAP LOVE.

1843
01:29:58,560 --> 01:29:59,492
CONGRATULATIONS!                
                    YEAH!

1844
01:29:59,561 --> 01:30:00,493
SHE'S PERFECT FOR YOU.

1845
01:30:00,562 --> 01:30:01,895
I KNEW IT.                      
I TOLD YOU.

1846
01:30:01,964 --> 01:30:03,796
THE CHEAPER THE BETTER.

1847
01:30:03,866 --> 01:30:05,598
AND SHE'S THE CHEAPEST.

1848
01:30:05,667 --> 01:30:07,600
YOUR NEXT PLAY IN PARIS?

1849
01:30:07,669 --> 01:30:08,768
PARIS!

1850
01:30:08,837 --> 01:30:11,571
YOU'RE LIKE A BITCH.            
YOU GO WHEREVER THE MONEY IS.

1851
01:30:11,639 --> 01:30:14,007
WITHOUT A WORD,                 
YOU BETRAY ME.

1852
01:30:14,076 --> 01:30:16,977
THAT'S IT. I'M NOT DOING
        YOUR PLAY TONIGHT.

1853
01:30:17,045 --> 01:30:19,579
YOU'RE NOT DOING                
HIS PLAY TONIGHT? WHY?

1854
01:30:19,647 --> 01:30:20,847
BECAUSE SHE'S NOT,  
            THAT'S WHY.

1855
01:30:20,916 --> 01:30:22,148
I'M NOT DOING IT.

1856
01:30:22,217 --> 01:30:23,283
NO, RACHEL, WAIT!

1857
01:30:23,352 --> 01:30:25,418
IT HAS NO ENDING!

1858
01:30:25,487 --> 01:30:26,586
WHAT?

1859
01:30:26,654 --> 01:30:29,389
SHE DOESN'T LEAVE HIM.  
        SHE DOESN'T HURT HIM.

1860
01:30:29,457 --> 01:30:31,191
SHE GOES ON LOVING HI!

1861
01:30:31,260 --> 01:30:33,459
BUT THAT'S WHAT'S               
GREAT ABOUT IT.

1862
01:30:33,528 --> 01:30:35,428
IT'S ONE BIG LIE!

1863
01:30:37,099 --> 01:30:40,433
YOU USED TO BE              
    SO DELICATE.

1864
01:30:40,502 --> 01:30:41,902
I USED TO THINK,

1865
01:30:41,970 --> 01:30:44,938
"IF I MOVE,                 
    I SHALL CRUSH HER."

1866
01:30:45,007 --> 01:30:46,839
DON'T.

1867
01:30:46,909 --> 01:30:48,741
YOU THINK THERE AREN'T      
    ANY OTHER ACTRESSES

1868
01:30:48,810 --> 01:30:50,593
AND COMPANIES WHO WANT      
    TO WORK WITH ME?

1869
01:30:50,662 --> 01:30:52,612
OF COURSE               
        THERE ARE!

1870
01:30:52,680 --> 01:30:55,015
HERE? OR IN PARIS,          
    FOR THAT MATTER?

1871
01:30:55,083 --> 01:30:58,385
OH, FUCK PARIS!                 
THEY'VE BEEN WRONG BEFORE.

1872
01:30:58,453 --> 01:30:59,786
YOU THINK YOU CAN           
    TEAR ME APART

1873
01:30:59,854 --> 01:31:01,554
THE WAY THIS ANIMAL 
            PALLENCHIO DOES?

1874
01:31:01,623 --> 01:31:03,723
I DID NOT!                      
NOT TO YOUR FACE! NEVER!

1875
01:31:03,792 --> 01:31:04,824
WHO TOLD YOU?

1876
01:31:04,893 --> 01:31:07,827
I HAVE A PLAY TO DELIVER    
    IN A MATTER OF HOURS.

1877
01:31:07,896 --> 01:31:10,496
YOU RAMBLE ON               
    ABOUT ANTARCTICA,

1878
01:31:10,565 --> 01:31:12,532
DOMINIQUE PLAYS             
    THE CONSPIRATOR,

1879
01:31:12,600 --> 01:31:13,934
AND PALLENCHIO              
    CONGRATULATES ME

1880
01:31:14,002 --> 01:31:15,835
FOR GOING TO A CITY         
    I'M NOT GOING TO

1881
01:31:15,904 --> 01:31:18,120
WITH AN ACTRESS           
      I'M NOT GOING WITH!

1882
01:31:20,192 --> 01:31:22,409
WHY WOULD I GO TO PARIS

1883
01:31:22,477 --> 01:31:24,210
AND NOT STAY HERE

1884
01:31:24,279 --> 01:31:27,180
WHERE I AM SO LOVED...

1885
01:31:27,249 --> 01:31:29,882
SO TRUSTED...

1886
01:31:29,952 --> 01:31:31,884
AND SO UNDERSTOOD?

1887
01:31:36,274 --> 01:31:38,624
IS HE STAYING                   
OR GOING?

1888
01:31:38,693 --> 01:31:40,493
IDIOT. HE STAYS.

1889
01:31:42,597 --> 01:31:44,431
RIGHT!                          
[CLAPS]

1890
01:31:44,499 --> 01:31:45,765
YOU HAVE WORK TO DO.

1891
01:31:45,834 --> 01:31:48,168
BUT PLEASE,                     
I IMPLORE YOU,

1892
01:31:48,236 --> 01:31:50,636
DON'T TOUCH                     
THAT ENDING!

1893
01:31:54,709 --> 01:31:56,742
TUCCIO.

1894
01:31:56,811 --> 01:31:58,511
TUCCIO.

1895
01:31:58,580 --> 01:32:00,880
I LOVE YOU.

1896
01:32:00,949 --> 01:32:02,349
WHAT?

1897
01:32:02,417 --> 01:32:05,118
I LOVE YOU.

1898
01:32:05,187 --> 01:32:07,687
YOU SAY THAT                    
AS IF YOU HAD STOPPED

1899
01:32:07,755 --> 01:32:09,689
AND WANTED                      
TO BEGIN AGAIN.

1900
01:32:09,757 --> 01:32:12,459
I NEVER STOPPED.

1901
01:32:12,527 --> 01:32:14,827
I DID NOTHING           
        EXCEPT TO LOVE YOU...

1902
01:32:16,631 --> 01:32:17,964
IMPERFECTLY.

1903
01:32:21,103 --> 01:32:22,402
I SPOKE FROM MY HEART,

1904
01:32:22,471 --> 01:32:27,307
AND IF I WAS WRONG,

1905
01:32:27,376 --> 01:32:29,075
I'VE BEEN WRONG BEFORE.

1906
01:32:31,679 --> 01:32:36,383
IT MEANS I'M            
        IMPERFECT, TUCCIO.

